AIM:
To locate and extract the Image with the Jpeg extension’s metadata through Exif Tool

PROCEDURE:

Step 1: Download Exif Tool from https://bit.ly/exif-tool 
Step 2: Download the exe file, Extract it and Open the Downloaded Folder to 
            Command-Line. 
Step 3: Type the command exiftool(-k).exe Example.jpeg (Here Copy the Path  
             of Jpeg(Image) file replace with Example.jpeg) 
Step 4: Jpeg File’s metadata will be displayed.
